The paper deals with computational and combinatorial aspects of graph drawings, which are typically studied in computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of computing line and plane cover numbers is related to graph theory (cs.DS) and geometric topology (cs.GT). Finally, the paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in computational complexity (cs.CC).
